  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><strong>Prerequisite</strong>: Guidance</em></p>\n<p>You touch a creature and enhance it with the Force. Choose one of the following effects; the target gains that effect until the power ends.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><em>Strength.</em></strong> The target has advantage on Strength checks, and his or her carrying capacity doubles.</li>\n<li><strong><em>Dexterity.</em></strong> The target has advantage on Dexterity checks. It also doesn't take damage from falling 20 feet or less if it isn't incapacitated.</li>\n<li><strong><em>Endurance.</em></strong> The target has advantage on Constitution checks. It also gains [[/r 2d6]] temporary hit points, which are lost when the power ends.</li>\n<li><strong><em>Cunning.</em></strong> The target has advantage on Intelligence checks.</li>\n<li><strong><em>Wisdom.</em></strong> The target has advantage on Wisdom checks.</li>\n<li><strong><em>Splendor.</em></strong> The target has advantage on Charisma checks.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This power has no effect on droids or constructs.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Force Potency.</em></strong> When you cast this power using a force slot of 3rd level or higher, you can target one additional creature for each slot level above 2nd.</p>",
